==Death==
[[File:Claude Monet 038.jpg|thumb|400px|''[[Water Lilies]]'', 1920-1926, [[Musée de l'Orangerie]]]]
Monet died of [[lung cancer]] on 5 December 1926 at the age of 86 and is buried in the [[Giverny]] church cemetery.&lt;ref&gt;[http://giverny.org/giverny/  The village of Giverny] giverny.org. Retrieved 6 January 2007.&lt;/ref&gt; Monet had insisted that the occasion be simple; thus only about fifty people attended the ceremony.&lt;ref&gt;P. Tucker ''Claude Monet: Life and Art'', p.224&lt;/ref&gt;

His home, garden and waterlily pond were bequeathed by his son Michel, his only heir, to the French Academy of Fine Arts (part of the [[Institut de France]]) in 1966. Through the ''Fondation Claude Monet'', the house and gardens were opened for visit in 1980, following restoration.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.fondation-monet.fr/uk/?q=content/historical-record |title=Historical record &amp;#124; |publisher=Fondation-monet.fr |date= |accessdate=2010-01-19}}&lt;/ref&gt; In addition to souvenirs of Monet and other objects of his life, the house contains his collection of [[Ukiyo-e|Japanese woodcut prints]]. The house is one of the two main attractions of [[Giverny]], which hosts tourists from all over the world.

==Posthumous sales==
[[File:Monet in Garden, New York Times, 1922.JPG|thumb|Monet, right, in his garden at [[Giverny]], 1922.]]

In 2004, ''[[London, the Parliament, Effects of Sun in the Fog]] (Londres, le Parlement, trouée de soleil dans le brouillard)'' (1904), sold for [[United States dollar|U.S. $]]20.1&amp;nbsp;million.&lt;ref&gt;[http://newsfromrussia.com/science/2004/11/05/57003.html Monet's masterpiece reaches record high bid] newsfromrussia.com, 5 November 2004. Retrieved 6 January 2007.&lt;/ref&gt; In 2006, the journal ''[[Proceedings of the Royal Society]]'' published a paper providing evidence that these were painted in situ at [[St Thomas' Hospital]] over the river [[Thames]].&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/monet/Tour_Thumbnails1/0,3992,209038,00.html |title=Unlimited |publisher=Guardian |date= |accessdate=2010-01-19 | location=London}}&lt;/ref&gt;

''Falaises près de Dieppe (Cliffs near Dieppe)'' has been stolen on two separate occasions. Once in 1998 (in which the museum's curator was convicted of the theft and jailed for five years and two months along with two accomplices) and most recently in August 2007.&lt;ref name=&quot;artforum&quot;&gt;{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = Art Forum | coauthors = | title = Monet and Others Stolen in Museum Heist in Nice | work = | publisher = artforum.com | date = 8 August 2007 | url = http://www.artforum.com/archive/id=15630 | doi = |accessdate=8 August 2007 }}&lt;/ref&gt; It was recovered in June 2008.&lt;ref name=&quot;msnrecovery&quot;&gt;{{cite web | last = | first = | authorlink = MSNBC | coauthors = | title = French police recover stolen Monet painting | work = | publisher = artforum.com | date = 1 October 2009 | url = http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/24973627/ | doi = |accessdate=1 October 2009 }}&lt;/ref&gt;

Monet's ''Le Pont du chemin de fer à Argenteuil,'' an 1873 painting of a [[railway bridge]] spanning the [[Seine]] near Paris, was bought by an anonymous telephone bidder for a record $ 41.4&amp;nbsp;million at [[Christie's]] auction in New York on 6 May 2008. The previous record for his painting stood at $ 36.5&amp;nbsp;million.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|author=(AFP) &amp;ndash; May 6, 2008 |url=http://afp.google.com/article/ALeqM5jJ-nuOHmXSBq7_MFQrllsC6jrt4A |title=Afp.google.com, Monet fetches record price at New York auction |publisher=Afp.google.com |date=2008-05-06 |accessdate=2010-01-19}}&lt;/ref&gt; ''[[Le bassin aux nymphéas]]'' (from the water lilies series) sold at Christie's 24 June 2008, lot 19,&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.christies.com/lotfinder/lot_details.aspx?intObjectID=5100003&amp;CID=5447010003801a|title=Le Bassin Aux Nymphéas|publisher=Christies of London|date=2008-06-24|accessdate=2008-06-24}}&lt;/ref&gt; for £36,500,000 ($71,892,376.34) (hammer price) or £40,921,250 ($80,451,178) with fees, setting a new auction record for the artist.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/7470832.stm|title=Monet work auctioned for £40.9m|publisher=BBC News|date=2008-06-24|accessdate=2008-06-24}}&lt;/ref&gt;

''Nympheas - Water Lilies'' sold for USD 71,846,600.
. This was one of the highest prices paid for Monet's work.&lt;ref&gt;[http://artsalesindex.artinfo.com/artsalesindex/aps/lots/10765152 Auction Result: Monet's ''Nympheas - Water Lilies'']{{dead link|date=January 2010}}&lt;/ref&gt;

